      Showing 5 of 5 replies
      • Sándor György7 months ago

      • Will T7 months ago

        I suspect there's a better way of doing this, but here's what I'm doing:

        1) In Calibre, right click on the book and select "Edit book"

        2) In the left sidebar, find "idGeneratedFiles.css" and double-click on it. (This will be easier to find if you collapse the "Text" section by clicking the little triangle next to it)

        3) At the very end of the file, add these lines:

        img[src^="image/wombat"], img[src^="image/ganesha"] {

        height: 90vh !important;

        width: auto !important;

        }

        4) File > Save (or Ctrl-S)

        Note that this will make the image expand so much that it covers up the page numbers at the bottom of each page when viewed as an Epub on desktop. There's probably a way to move the page numbers out of the way, but it might require bigger changes to the file. After converting the file to Mobi, the page numbers move to the top anyway, so it's not an issue on Kindle.

        You can edit the number "90" in those lines to tweak the size - if you find the images are getting cut off at the edges, you can make it smaller, and if there's too much margin, you can try making it bigger (but don't set it bigger than 100). 90 was a pretty good fit on my Paperwhite.

        While testing this out, I found that SumatraPDF, my favorite PDF viewer, expands images automatically without doing any of this, so that could also be an option if you aren't committed to Calibre.

      • Scott KullbergSuperbacker7 months ago

      • Grim Oak PressCreator11 months ago

        To update your pledge:

        1. Click Manage Pledge. The Reward page is displayed with your pledge information.

        2. Click Change Your Pledge. The Select Your Reward page is displayed.

        3. Click the green button showing your current pledge amount. You can now add on stuff.

        4. Click Add next to anything you want to add to your pledge/purchase. The total changes to reflect what you are now getting.

        5. Click Continue to update your pledge.

        6. Dance in impatient anticipation until the goodies arrive.
